{"key":"processedPost-4607178","value":{"id":4607178,"first":4589071,"last":4609097,"when":1125572453,"utime":"09/01/05 02:00 PM","content":"If the molds are growing throughout the jar, it would most likely be the sterilization process.  If the molds are growing from the inoculation points, they were introduced later, either through not sterilizing the needle, or a contaminated syringe.  Always use a glovebox if you don't have a flowhood.  Remember, mold and bacteria are everywhere in the air around you, and when you breathe and especially when you talk, millions of bacteria leave your mouth. A glovebox will help to protect your project from yourself. We as cultivators are the biggest source of contaminants.<br />RR","title":"Re: Green mold pls help","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}